[SN]TITLE[SN]
Probe after taser fired at Hunterston nuclear plant

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An investigation has been launched after a taser was fired at a police station within a Scots nuclear plant.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Police Investigations and Review Commissioner said it was "investigating the unintentional discharge" at the Hunterston facility in North Ayrshire.
The incident took place on 7 March at the Civil Nuclear Constabulary station.
The force is a specialist armed police service that is dedicated to protecting 14 civil nuclear sites across Scotland, England and Wales.
A report will be submitted to the Civil Nuclear Constabulary deputy chief constable in due course.
